<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0453</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Drench Mississippi Valley, northern Plains</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Strong thunderstorms moved across the upper Mississippi Valley
and the northern Plains early today, while rain continued to soak
New England.
   In South Dakota, hail an inch in diameter covered the ground at
Avon and marble-size hail fell on Brookings.
   Thunderstorms were diminishing over the northern Rockies after
one storm dumped more than a third of an inch of rain in two
minutes at Pony, Mont.
   Elsewhere, showers and thunderstorms, some with locally heavy
rainfall, extended from the Texas panhandle into central Oklahoma.
Between 1 and 2{ inches of rain drenched the Oklahoma City, Okla.,
area Sunday night.
   Strong thunderstorms scattered over southern New Mexico downed
power lines near Hobbs. Strong thunderstorms also were scattered
across the upper Great Lakes.
   An upper air disturbance triggered showers and thunderstorms
with heavy rains over New England. More than 2 inches of rain fell
Sunday in Boston.
   Heavier rainfall during the six hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT
included more than 2{ inches at Oklahoma City, Okla., nearly 1{
inches at Burlington, Vt., and more than an inch at Eau Claire,
Wis., and Spencer, Iowa.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms over Iowa,
the upper Great Lakes, Florida and much of the Atlantic Coast; and
scattered showers and thunderstorms from central Texas into
Oklahoma and across the northern Rockies.
   Highs were expected to be in the 60s from northeast Minnesota
into upper Michigan; in the 70s in the northern Plains, the upper
Mississippi Valley, the upper Great Lakes, northern Maine and the
northern Pacific Coast; in the 90s in southern Florida, the western
Gulf Coast, southern Texas and the southern Rockies; in the 100s in
the desert Southwest and interior valleys of California; and in the
80s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 49
degrees at Yellowstone Park in Wyoming to 97 degrees at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   EAST _ Atlanta 75 partly cloudy; Boston 72 cloudy; Buffalo 62
fair; Cleveland 65 fair; Detroit 63 foggy; Miami 76 fair; New York
71 foggy; Philadelphia 72 foggy; Portland, Maine 68 foggy; and
Washington 72 foggy.
   CENTRAL _ Bismarck 62 cloudy; Denver 60 fair; Fort Worth 78
cloudy; Indianapolis 64 foggy; Kansas City 62 foggy; Little Rock 66
foggy; Louisville 65 hazy; Nashville 65 fair; New Orleans 70 foggy;
St. Louis 72 hazy; and Minneapolis-St. Paul 64 cloudy.
   WEST _ Albuquerque 68 fair; Las Vegas 88 fair; Phoenix 96 fair;
Portland 63 cloudy; Salt Lake City 74 partly cloudy; San Francisco
57 fair; and Seattle 64 cloudy.
   CANADA _ Montreal 70 foggy; and Toronto 59 foggy.
</TEXT>
