<FIRST>r a PM-ScreamsIgnored 1stLd-Writethru   08-14 0253</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Screams Ignored, 1st Ld - Writethru,0256</SECOND>
<HEAD>Woman Slain, Neighbors Ignore Screams</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: RECASTS lead, moves up quote, edits throughout. No pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman was beaten and stabbed to death in her
apartment as neighbors listened to her screams without going to
help, police said.
   Ruth Velez, 39, was repeatedly stabbed in the abdomen with her
own kitchen knife and beaten on the head, police said. No one
called the police emergency number until 11 p.m. Saturday, an hour
after the screams were first heard.
   ``Someone should have done something sooner,'' said Stella
Schectman, the owner of the three-family house in a comfortable,
middle-class section of Brooklyn.
   A neighbor who finally went to the victim's second-floor
apartment an hour after the violence began found Velez, a computer
programmer, dead amid a clutter of smashed furniture and overturned
house plants. Police said the assailant may have been a robber, and
they were questioning several people.
   Schectman said she returned from an errand in the middle of the
attack to find several neighbors gathered in the street.
   ``They said there was a lot of screaming coming from Ruth's
apartment. So I asked, why didn't someone go knock on her door? But
they were afraid,'' she said.
   Schectman then went to her apartment, separated by a thin wall
from Velez's, and watched television.
   ``I heard noises and heavy footsteps from Ruth's apartment. She
never had men in her apartment, but I knew she wasn't alone. Then
it was quiet,'' Schectman said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
