<HEAD>Names in the News</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS Boston-dated 4th item to CORRECT by deleting that Michael
Kennedy is Robert F. Kennedy's oldest son.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Michael Kennedy, son of the late Robert F. Kennedy,
has rounded up tons of medical supplies, thousands of sneakers and
two congressmen for a trip to Africa.
   Kennedy said the trip leaving Tuesday for Angola, Namibia and the
Congo had political as well as humanitarian aims.
   ``We are showing a gesture from America that we are truly
interested in that part of the world,'' said Kennedy, 31, chairman
of the nonprofit Citzens Energy Corp.
   Kennedy's mother, Ethel, and wife, Vicki, planned to accompany
him on the trip through an area his father visited in the 1960s.
   ``When I travel over there, he is so well remembered,'' Kennedy
said.
   The entourage includes Reps. Mike Espy, D-Miss., and Paul Henry,
R-Mich., and a group of oil and telecommunications executives. The
group will meet with Angolan President Jose Eduardo do Santos and
other leaders.
