<HEAD>NBC News to Close Paris Bureau</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   NBC News says it will close its Paris bureau by
the end of the year and use some of the money it saves to bolster
coverage of the Soviet Union and Eastern Europe.
   NBC News President Michael Gartner announced last week that the
network also would open a bureau in Barcelona, Spain, as part of its
plans to televise the 1992 summer Olympics, and a bureau in Dallas
to cover the southwestern United States.
   Ted Elbert, the Paris bureau chief, will head the Moscow bureau,
which will be operated jointly with the British Broadcasting Corp.
and Visnews. The network also will open a bureau in Budapest,
Gartner said.
