<HEAD>Satellite Station Opens in Vietnam</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vietnam is expanding its international
telecommunication links via another Australian-built satellite earth
station, the Vietnam News Agency said in a dispatch seen Monday.
   The station, named Saigon-1A, was inaugurated Saturday in Ho Chi
Minh City and was the third such project between Australia's
Overseas Telecommunication Commission and the Vietnamese government.
   The agency said the new earth station alllows Vietnam to broaden
its telecommunications services to many countries in the world
through the Intelsat Satellite System.
   Stations in Hanoi and the central Vietnam city of Danang will go
into operation this year, the news agency said. The first station
under the cooperation agreement was opened in Ho Chi Minh City in
1987 and a second started operation in Hanoi this year.
