<HEAD>New Editor for Delaware Paper</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Henry M. Freeman, managing editor for sports of
USA Today, has been appointed editor of the Wilmington (Del.) News
Journal, the Gannett Co. announced Monday.
   Freeman will succeed J. Donald Brandt, who will join USA Today's
editorial board as a regional editor, said Peter S. Prichard, editor
of USA Today and senior vice president for news for Gannett.
   Freeman, 42, has been at USA Today since 1982, before the
newspaper began publication. He had previously been assistant sports
editor at the News Journal and was an assistant managing editor at
the Oakland, Calif., Tribune before moving to USA Today.
   Brandt, 60, has been at the News Journal since 1961 and has been
editor for the past six years.
