<HEAD>Remains of Air Force Colonel Identified</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The remains of U.S. Air Force Col. Don I.
Williamson, who was killed in Vietnam, have been identified and will
be returned to the United States on Tuesday, the Pentagon announced.
   Williamson, of Louisville, Ky., was reported missing on July 7,
1965, the Pentagon said in a statement.
   His remains were among 25 remains turned over to U.S. officials
by the Vietnamese government in January. Three of the remains have
been identified at the U.S. Army Central Indentification Lab in
Honolulu.
   The remains are scheduled to depart Hickam Air Force Base in
Hawaii on Tuesday, with full military honors, and to be transported
to Travis Air Force Base in California, the statement said.
