<HEAD>President Signs Resolutions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush signed resolutions Monday
declaring:
   _The week of Sept. 1-7 as ``World War II Remembrance Week.''
   _The week of Sept. 3-9 as ``National Wilderness Week.''
   _The week of Oct. 1-7 as ``Mental Illness Awareness Week.''
   The World War II resolution originated in the House, the other
two in the Senate.
   Congress and the president customarily designate scores of weeks
and days on behalf of various causes, events and other happenings
each year.
   In some cases, as with World War II Remembrance Week and National
Wilderness Week, they overlap.
