<FIRST>r a AM-FairStabbing 1stLd-Writethru a0699 08-14 0381</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Fair Stabbing, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0699,0385</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mental Patient Found Competent to Stand Trial for Fair Stabbing</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 3rd graf to restore Peterson's first name.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LARRY ROSENTHAL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MIDDLETOWN, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mental patient accused of fatally
stabbing a 9-year-old girl at a street fair after walking away from
a state hospital was found competent Monday to stand trial.
   Superior Court Judge Donald T. Dorsey accepted the unananimous
finding of competency by an examining panel made up of a
psychiatrist, psychologist and psychiatric social worker.
   The panel noted that David Peterson suffers from mental illness
and experiences delusions of persecution, but said the problems do
not compromise his ability to understand the charges against him and
to help in his own defense.
   Peterson, 37, had been committed to the state's care in 1988
after being found innocent by reason of insanity in the stabbing of
a neighbor in a rooming house.
   Peterson, who kept his eyes lowered during the 10-minute hearing,
was wearing a large bandage over his right hand and wrist. His
attorney, Assistant Public Defender Chris James, said he believed
Peterson had suffered the injury when he was arrested after the July
28 knife attack.
   Asked how Peterson has been acting since the slaying, James would
only say, ``He's a very sick young man.''
   James waived a hearing on the competency issue, but said he would
request that Peterson be re-examined before trial because competency
``is a day- to-day thing.''.
   The judge scheduled a probable cause hearing for Sept. 12.
Peterson was arrested on murder and weapons charges.
   Peterson walked off the grounds of Connecticut Valley Hospital in
Middletown on July 28, took a bus to downtown and bought a hunting
knife. He then went to a crowded street fair, where he attacked
9-year-old Jessica Short at random while her mother and several
other people looked on, police said.
   The attack lasted less than a minute, ending when police officers
and a bystander pulled Peterson away from the girl. She was stabbed
repeatedly in the face and chest and died less than an hour later.
   Peterson is now being held at the Whiting Forsensic Institute,
the maximum-security facility in Middletown for criminally insane
mental patients. Dorsey ordered that bond remain at $750,000.
</TEXT>
