<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 2pm,0284</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices were mixed in relatively slow
trading today with blue-chip issues showing the most strength.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was up 7.78 points to
2,691.77 at 2 p.m. EDT. The blue-chip indicator was down 0.95 point
at noon after a choppy morning session.
   Declining issues outpaced advances by about 4 to 3 on the New
York Stock Exchange, with 808 issues up, 594 down and 515 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 95.08 million shares.
   Blue-chip stocks led the way in afternoon trading with the
broader market lagging behind, analysts said.
   ``We do have strength in the market today but it is a
narrow-based rally,'' said Charles Jensen, chief technical analyst
for MKI Securities Corp.
   Profit-taking carried over from late Friday helped depress prices
early in the day in fairly light trading. The market crept up slowly
at mid-morning then turned flat around midday before resuming a slow
climb.
   Analysts said the market could pick up more momentum later in the
week when the government reports on housing starts, merchandise
trade and consumer prices.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was up
0.12 at 192.34.
   At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index was off
0.51 to 380.13.
   Among actively traded issues on the NYSE, Hewlett Packard was
down 2| at 52|, Paramount Communications was off ~ at 60] and
General Electric had lost \ at 57].
   IBM, meanwhile, was up | to 116[, Eastman Kodak was up } at 50}
and Exxon had gained 1 to 44|.
