<HEAD>Stock Exchanges to Study Link to Equity Options Markets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three stock exchanges on Monday announced
that they will study the possibility of linking equity options
markets electronically.
   The Philadelphia Stock Exchange, the Pacific Stock Exchange and
the New York Stock Exchange have commissioned Tellefsen Consulting
Group Inc. of New York to study the feasibility of the electronic
system.
   The study is scheduled to be completed in early September.
Results will likely be included in comments to the Securities and
Exchange Commission, which has a Sept. 18 deadline for public
comment on its white paper on options market linkages.
