<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-Playboy     08-14 0239</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-Playboy,0248</SECOND>
<HEAD>Playboy Posts $3.8 Million Loss for Fiscal 89</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Playboy Enterprises Inc. on Monday reported losses
for the final quarter and all of fiscal 1989 due to costs of changes
in the company's cable television channel, organizational
restructuring and relocation of corporate headquarters.
   The net loss for the three months ending June 30 was $6 million,
compared to a loss of $5.1 million for the same period a year ago.
Net sales and revenues were $39.6 million for the fourth quarter,
down from $37.8 million for last year's period.
   For the entire fiscal year, Playboy reported a loss of $3.8
million, compared to a gain of $2.6 million for fiscal 1988. Revenue
for the year rose to $166.2 million from $159.8 million.
   ``While there was a cost to our actions which hurt fiscal 1989
results, we have appropriately and aggressively begun to make
investments that will grow this company into the 1990s,'' said
Christie Hefner, chairman and chief executive officer.
   On Aug. 3, the company announced it will change the marketing of
The Playboy Channel, renaming it ``Playboy at Night'' and offering
it on a pay-per-view basis. The channel has been offered on a
pay-per-night basis.
   Playboy also will be moving into new corporate headquarters in
Chicago this fall.
   The company reported that Playboy magazine had a 12 percent gain
in advertising pages and a 16 percent gain in advertising revenues
during the year.
</TEXT>
